==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[leger|leġer]] ‘couch, bed’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /lɛ:/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛə(r)|-ɛə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A place [[inhabit]]ed by a [[wild]] [[animal]], often a [[cave]] or a hole in the ground.
# (''figuratively'') A place inhabited by a criminal or criminals.

====Synonyms====
*(''of an animal''): [[burrow]] (''of some smaller mammals''), [[den]] (''of a lion or tiger'')
*(''of a criminal''): [[den]], [[hide-out]]

